Here's a summary of the repository:

Project: Housing Priority Calculator (CS2100 HW1)
Purpose
A TDD (Test-Driven Development) learning assignment where students build a housing priority scoring system for students. The system asks users questions about their class year, graduation status, and credits earned, then calculates a priority score to fairly allocate limited housing resources.

Project Structure
src/hw1.py — Main orchestration module
src/question_asker.py — HousingQuestionAsker class: handles user input with validation
src/priority_calculator.py — HousingPriorityCalculator class: computes priority scores
tests/ — Test files (interface + implementation-specific tests)
Summary.md — Template for documenting scoring rationale
How to Run

pip install -r requirements.txt        # Install deps

python3 test_runner.py                 # Run all tests
python3 test_runner.py -t test_hw1.py  # Run specific test file

python3 hw1.py                         # Run the app manually

./generate_coverage_reports.sh         # Generate HTML coverage report
Libraries & Tools
Library/Tool	Purpose
unittest	Testing framework (stdlib)
unittest.mock.patch	Mock input() calls in tests
coverage	Code coverage measurement
pylint	Static analysis/linting
mypy	Type checking (strict mode, via VS Code)
GitHub Actions	Automated grading via Pawtograder CI
Key Design Pattern
Separation of concerns: input validation (HousingQuestionAsker) is decoupled from scoring logic (HousingPriorityCalculator). Students must design their own point system (class year, graduation status, credits, 2 custom yes/no questions), write tests first, then implement.

